           <!-- [The following two letters are written by Monroe Thayer, Co. C. 10th Mass. Vol. to his friend, Rufus.] -->   
            
            <div1 type="letter" id="d3">
            	<pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0071"/>
            	<head>Monroe Thayer to Friend Rufus <date value="1863-12-22">Dec 22<hi rend="super">nd</hi> 1863</date></head>
            	
            <opener>	
            <dateline><name type="place">Camp Near Brandol Station</name><lb/>
            <date value="1863-12-22">Dec 22<hi rend="super">nd</hi> 1863</date><lb/>
            </dateline>
            	
            <salute>Friend Rufus</salute>
            </opener>
            	
            <p>	
            I have a little time<lb/>
            to Spare this Morning and I<lb/>
            thought I Would Write you<lb/>
            a few lines I Saw William<lb/>
            last night and he told me<lb/>
            to tell you to Send him his<lb/>
            Watch if you had it fixed up<lb/>
            in good Shape he Sends his<lb/>
            Respects to you and all the<lb/>
            folks We ar<!--[e]--> all Well and I<lb/>
            hope my letter Will find<lb/>
            you the Same there is a<lb/> 
            good maney Inlisting out<lb/>
            of our Regt But I Don't<lb/>
            think I had Better Inlist<lb/>
            Because I think that three<lb/>
            years is a nough for me I<lb/>
            Will Stay on untill my time
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0072" n="[page 2]"/>
            	
            is out and then I Will go<lb/>
            home and Behave my Self<lb/>
            I think three years is anough<lb/>
            for any man in the Army<lb/>
            if I Was in your Place I<lb/>
            Would never Inlist I Suppose<lb/>
            you know What you told<lb/>
            me When I left home you<lb/>
            told me that I Would Be Sorrow<lb/>
            for Ever Inlisting and I have ben<lb/>
            Sorrow Many a time if I<lb/>
            Ever live to See Massachusetts<lb/>
            Again I Will never leve the State<lb/>
            I got up this Morning and I<lb/>
            Put on my Shoes made a fire<lb/>
            and Went About a half a mile<lb/>
            to get Some Watter to Make<lb/>
            my Coffie I made my Coffie<lb/>
            and Before I got my Brekfast<lb/>
            Eat I Was Detailed to go and<lb/>
            Work for the General I Worked<lb/>
            About Six hours and then Went
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0073" n="[page 3]"/>
            	
            to my Company and as Soon<lb/>
            as I got my Dinner Eat I<lb/>
            Was Sent to the Woods to Chop<lb/>
            Wood for the Company.
            </p>
            <p>
            I Would like Soldiering Very<lb/>
            Well if I Could onley have<lb/>
            What I Wanted I Don't like<lb/>
            to get up in the night and<lb/>
            march 15 &mdash; or 20 Miles Before <del hand="author" rend="line-through">Brekfas</del><lb/>
            Brekfast and Before Dinner,<lb/>
            go Into a Battle an lay in<lb/>
            line all the next if you Can <lb/>
            Escape the Draft I Should <del hand="author" rend="line-through">Advise</del><lb/>
            Advise you to do So Seven<lb/>
            Hundred Dolars is a good Sum<lb/>
            But I don't think it is<lb/>
            Anough for me I Don't think<lb/>
            I Would Inlist for Seven thousand<lb/>
            Dolars if' I get out of this<lb/>
            Armey I Will Inlist again I must<lb/>
            Close for now Give my love to<lb/>
            all the folks <del hand="author" rend="line-through">Good</del> 
            </p>
            	
            <pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0074" n="[page 4]"/>
            
            <closer>
            <salute>Good Bye<lb/>
            	From your Friend for
            Ever.</salute>
            <signed>Monroe , Thayer<lb/>
            Co, C. 10<hi rend="super">th</hi> Mass. Vol<lb/>
            Washington<lb/>
            D C </signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">Please Send me Some Postagestamps</seg>
            </closer>
            	
            	</div1>
